                <note rend="inline" type="source">561.311D1/8: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dawes</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-04-25T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 25, 1931—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>105. Your 119, April 24, 3 p.m. I have been informed by our Legation at Ottawa
                    that the Canadian Government is in the process of transmitting an official
                    invitation to this Government to participate in this Conference. It is hoped
                    that a decision in regard to this matter will be reached next week and an
                    official reply forwarded to the Canadian Government. When this is done I shall
                    telegraph you in order that you may informally advise Mr. Ferguson of the
                    decision which has been reached. It is my desire that any communications in
                    regard to this matter with London should pass through the Embassy and this
                    Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
